        <h5>
            Named Entity Recognition (NER) is a process in natural language processing (NLP) that identifies and classifies key entities in text into predefined categories such as names of people, organizations, locations, dates, and more.
            <br><br>
            For certificates, an NER description might focus on identifying specific elements typically found in such documents. Hereâ€™s a basic breakdown of how NER might be applied to certificates:
            <br><br>
            Example: "John Doe" - Issuer Name: The name of the entity issuing the certificate.
            <br><br>
            Example: "Acme Corporation" - Certificate Title: The title or type of certificate issued.
            <br><br>
            Example: "Certificate of Completion" - Date of Issue: The date when the certificate was issued.
            <br><br>
            Example: "July 29, 2024" - Date of Expiry: The date when the certificate expires, if applicable.
            <br><br>
            Example: "July 29, 2025" - Certificate Number: A unique identifier for the certificate.
            <br><br>
            Example: "Jane Smith, Director of Operations" - Location: The location where the certificate was issued.
